column4: displayName
ProMetaS Machine Learning Metadata:Model Metadata
description
Unique Identifier id for the Model. (eg: MML1)
Name for Model Metadata (entry) (eg: Model1)
Version of the model. (eg Version 1)
A machine learning framework where the model is created. (eg Tensorflow)
Version of the framework, mentioned in From Framework (eg Tensorflow 2.3)
Identifier of the dataset on which this model has been trained (eg: **doi of datasetID**)
Algorithm to find the parameter of the model. (eg: Adam Optimizer)
Parameters of model or training (eg: no. of layers, activation function ,etc). It could be array of parameters with their value and can be of multiple replication.
Hyperparameter Term Name
Hyperparameter value associated with the term
Storage location of your model. (example: Local machine or url)
Data pre-processing transformations applied to the data before going as inputs into the model. It might be different feature transformations (eg linearisation, normalisation or scaling steps)
Transform Term Name
Transform Term Value

Task is a formal description of a process that needs to be completed (e.g. Classification of a flow regime in the reactor or prediction of pressure drop within next 5 minutes in a distillation column).

column3: Model Metadata: Characteristics of Input Layer
column4: The shape of input data. In case of a neural network it would mean the shape of the input layer. Recommended to use numpy shape notation (eg: (255,255,1) for gray-scale image or (5) for an array with 5 predictors)
column5: Eg: (255,255,1) for gray-scale image or (5) for an array with 5 predictors

column3: Model Metadata: Characteristics of Output Layer
column4: The shape of model output if applied. In case if a neural network it would mean the shape of the output layer. Recommended to use numpy shape notation. (eg: (3) for a classification task with 3 classes according to the one-hot scheme)
column5: eg: (3) for a classification task with 3 classes according to the one-hot scheme

column4: Total number of free model parameters. For a neural network, it would mean the overall number of trainable weights and biases. (eg 10)
Additional Info for your model (eg Tags)
identifier
